---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  date: 'January 17, 2024',
  tool1: {
    name: 'Framer AI',
    slug: '/reviews/framer-ai'
  },
  tool2: {
    name: 'Durable',
    slug: '/reviews/durable-ai'
  }
};

const quickVerdict = {
    framer: 'Best for design quality and portfolios',
    durable: 'Best for speed and simplicity',
    winner: 'Framer for design, Durable for speed'
};
---

<Layout title="Framer AI vs Durable: Quality vs Speed">

  <!-- WebPage Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="WebPage"
    data={{
      name: 'Framer AI vs Durable: Quality vs Speed',
      description: 'Framer produces beautiful sites but takes longer. Durable generates sites in seconds with simpler design. Quality vs speed trade-off.',
      url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/comparisons/framer-vs-durable'
    }}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO - Coupon site style -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <!-- Geometric accent -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              {comparisonData.date} · COMPARISON
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">Framer AI vs Durable:</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">Quality vs Speed</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              I spent 26 hours testing both. Built multiple sites on each. One gives stunning designs you can't export. The other generates functional sites in 30 seconds that look dated.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content wrapper -->
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <article class="px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-[#F5521A]/5 border-l-4 border-[#F5521A] p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-gray-900">
            <strong>The one-sentence answer:</strong><br />
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Use Framer if you care about design.</strong> Portfolios, marketing sites, anything visual. Slower and more expensive, but the output is gorgeous.<br /><br />
            <strong class="text-gray-900">Use Durable if you care about speed.</strong> Local businesses, MVPs, quick validation. Not pretty, but live in under a minute.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The fundamental difference</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Framer and Durable sit at opposite ends of the AI builder spectrum. Framer prioritizes design quality and customization. Durable prioritizes speed and simplicity.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>Framer:</strong> Generate a site in 2-5 minutes, then spend 2-4 hours refining. You get pixel-perfect control over everything. The result looks like a professional designer built it.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>Durable:</strong> Generate a complete site in 28 seconds. Done. What you see is basically what you get. Limited customization, but it's live and functional.
        </p>

        <div class="my-8 p-6 bg-gray-100 border-[3px] border-gray-300 border-[3px]">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm">
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Framer AI:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.framer}</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Durable AI:</div>
              <p class="text-gray-900">{quickVerdict.durable}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-300">
            <strong>Verdict:</strong> {quickVerdict.winner}
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Quick comparison</h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Metric</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Framer AI</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900 font-black">Durable</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600 font-medium">Winner</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Design quality</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">9.2/10</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">6.5/10</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Generation speed</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">3-5 minutes</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">28 seconds</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Durable</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Ease of use</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">7/10</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">9/10</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Durable</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Customization</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">9.5/10</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">4/10</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">PageSpeed score</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">98/100</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">85/100</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-300">
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Export options</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$25/month tier</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">None</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Framer</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-600">Monthly cost</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$15-25</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-gray-900">$12-20</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-4 text-green-600 font-medium">Durable</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Framer wins</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Stunning designs</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Framer's AI understands spacing, typography, and visual hierarchy. The generated sites look like a human designer spent hours on them. Smooth animations, thoughtful micro-interactions, professional polish.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Durable's designs look functional. Generic business templates. Nothing offensive, but nothing memorable. If your brand is design-driven, Framer is the only choice.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Full customization</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Move anything anywhere. Change fonts, colors, animations. Framer's visual editor feels like using Figma—predictable and powerful. You can create custom hover states, scroll animations, complex interactions.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Durable lets you change colors and swap content, but that's about it. Layout changes are limited. If Framer gives you 100% control, Durable gives you 20%.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Excellent performance</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          My test sites: Framer at 98/100 PageSpeed, loads in under 1 second. Durable at 85/100, loads in ~1.5s. Both are fast, but Framer is exceptional—better Core Web Vitals, smoother interactions.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Interaction designer</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Framer has a built-in tool for creating animations and micro-interactions. Hover effects, scroll animations, page transitions—designed visually, no code needed. Durable has none of this.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Where Durable wins</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Lightning fast</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          28 seconds to a live site. Not "ready to customize"—actually live. Name your business, answer 3 questions, hit generate. Done. Framer can't match this speed.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Very simple</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          No learning curve. Generate and done. My 65-year-old dad built his contractor site in Durable without help. Framer takes 2-3 hours to learn the basics.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Built-in CRM</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Email tools, contact management, invoicing—all included. Framer is just a website builder. Durable is trying to be a business platform. If you need simple CRM, Durable wins.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Affordable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          $12/month vs $15-25 for Framer. Not a huge difference, but every dollar counts for small businesses. And Durable includes more features at that price.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>The lock-in problem</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>Both have the same fatal flaw: you can't leave.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Framer lets you export, but only on the $25/month plan. And even then, you're exporting React code tied to Framer's ecosystem—not portable HTML/CSS. If you leave, you're rebuilding.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Durable doesn't export at all. Your site lives on their servers, uses their platform, and if you stop paying, it disappears. Period.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 my-8">
          <p class="text-sm">
            <strong>Bottom line:</strong> If building a long-term business asset matters to you, neither tool is ideal. But if you're testing an idea or need something live tomorrow, they're both fine—just know you're renting, not owning.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>So which should you use?</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Framer if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You're a designer or creative professional</li>
          <li>Design quality matters more than speed</li>
          <li>You need animations and micro-interactions</li>
          <li>You're building a portfolio or marketing site</li>
          <li>You're willing to spend 2-3 hours learning</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Durable if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You're a local business (plumber, dentist, bakery)</li>
          <li>You need a site live in under 5 minutes</li>
          <li>You don't care about design awards</li>
          <li>You're testing an MVP or business idea</li>
          <li>You want built-in CRM and email tools</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose neither if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You need e-commerce (use 10Web)</li>
          <li>You want to own your code (use WordPress)</li>
          <li>You're on a tight budget (use free options)</li>
          <li>You're doing white-label client work</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>Bottom line</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Framer makes the prettiest sites. If design matters, pay the extra and deal with the learning curve. Your site will look professional.<br /><br />
          Durable makes sites fastest. If you just need something online now and don't care about aesthetics, it's perfect for that.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <strong>They're not competitors.</strong> Framer is for design-led projects. Durable is for speed-led projects. Pick based on what matters more: how it looks or how fast it's live.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 my-12">
          <a href={comparisonData.tool1.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Read Framer review
          </a>
          <a href={comparisonData.tool2.slug} class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-300 text-gray-900 font-medium hover:border-[#F5521A] hover:text-[#F5521A] transition-colors">
            Read Durable review
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
